In article <gradyCG5DpG.7zs@netcom.com> grady@netcom.com (Grady Ward) writes:
> While it is true can you can make any arbitrary channel
> or channels leakproof, you have to translate to clear
> at some (perhaps within the CPU or at the IO bus or
> at the disk controller or whatever) point.
> 
> I am lookng forward to every distinguishable entity
> associated with a computer: io channels, cpu, coprocessors,
> processor cache, video bus, ISDN lines, processes,
> everything -- having individual public keys and using RSA
> internally to decode instructions and logic.
> 
> You could have perfectly secure virtual computing behemoths
> spanning continents perhaps using whatever resources it
> needed and delivering results in perfect privacy.
> 
