> Grady Ward          | compiler of:            | "Look!"


The ultimate, of course, would be to implant a chip in your head that decrypts  
the cyphertext you're looking at and projects the cleartext onto your retina.

However, reversing the process (thinking in cleartext and typing out  
cyphertext) is still a problem. :-)

